    • Method Detail

      • emptyInstance

        public static SearchResult emptyInstance()
        Returns an empty search result with a zero-size phrase array and whose status code is set to SearchResult.Status.OK. The empty result can be used instead of null to represent the absence of a result and/or to reduce null checks in client code.

      • getPhrases

        public Phrase[] getPhrases()
        Returns the matching phrases. If a request was not successful or the result set is empty, an empty array is returned, i.e. no null check required.
